Critical audit complete. I wrote my findings to `notes/CR-FRAC-21-Claude-Critical-20260605-1547.md`, covering all 7 scope areas with `file:line` cites, read-only (no source touched, no build commands), and respecting the FRAC-20 carve-out on the face-tint *values*.

**The five things I'd block a merge on:**

1. **No single source of truth for house accent color.** `houses.ts color` (still read live by `AvatarBadge`/`BadgePlayground`), `HouseBanner.ELEGANT_PAIRS`, and the hero `OUTER_NAV_NODES` give the *same house three different hues*. The banner+hero were migrated (FRAC-17); the data model was left behind.

2. **`Button` is built on undefined Replit artifacts.** `hover-elevate`, `active-elevate-2`, `--button-outline`, and the `*-border` tokens exist nowhere in this repo — so button hover/active elevation and the outline-variant border are **silent no-ops**. The primary CTA has no real hover feedback.

3. **`FractalObject.tsx` is dead code** carrying the *old* palette, and its export name collides with the live component (which actually lives in `OctahedronHero.tsx`). Filename and export point at different implementations — a trap for the next editor.

4. **`prefers-reduced-motion` is honored in exactly one place** (node glow). Octahedron rotation, the scrolling edge texture, and every Framer-Motion `FadeIn` reveal ignore it — and `FadeIn` wraps most page content.

5. **Cream + token rot:** stale `#f7f6f2` comment, the body background token is never actually shown in the hero (hero hardcodes a different `#faf8f5`), `--font-sans` and `--font-mono` resolve to the *same* family, and the entire `.dark` block (~28 tokens) is unwired (no ThemeProvider/toggle anywhere).

Secondary but notable: `.link-underline`, `.animate-blink`, and `.hero-text-shadow` are all **zero-reference dead utilities**; muted-foreground (~4.0:1) and the hero placeholder (~2:1) fail WCAG AA on the noised cream; lab purple `#6B4C9A` is hardcoded 11× instead of tokenized; and `px-[4.5%]` vs `px-6/8/4` plus eleven distinct `max-w-*` values mean there's no real container/spacing scale.

I did not write to Lattice or run any commands per the audit's read-only constraints — that orchestration is the parent task's job.
